This paper is primarily focused on face detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of adversarial training and segmentation techniques also suggests that this paper may fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) categories due to the focus on occlusion and masquerade detection.
